,
only concealing my name.
I was preparing to leave the room, when a child
entered, whom I
instantly
knew to be my little
petitioner
I
will
see
thee again to-morrow,
said
I
but will now
seek
my lovely Emma, and engage her
in thy behalf.
The RESOLUTION.
It
was more than I could conveniently afford,
said
Iwhen I found how much money I had expended
Twenty pounds is a good
sum
, but it will
cost
me
much more before I have placed Heartfree in a
situation
more
suitable
to his meritbut no matter, I
will
discharge
one of my
