was obliged to
bestow
on this
darling of the family,
soon
made him think he was
as learned as any of the
seven
wife men of Greece,
and therefore had no farther need of a preceptor.
When I found he grew
careless
and neglectful,
I thought a little correction might be
necessary
; but,
on trying the experiment, was called by the over fond
mother, an inhuman
