, and
going down, told her, that her uncle being rather
indisposed
,
desired
not to be
disturbed
.
On pretence of going for an apothecary I went
and informed an intimate friend of Maria's with the
melancholy affair. We determined
she
should
call
and take Maria out, and by various methods keep
her from home all day; when in the evening we
would, by degrees, acquaint her with the
sad
