for, indeed Sir,
said
she
, I heartily forgive himI
do not
wish
his death now, though once I
sought
to
have
assassinated
him; but I have
since
been taught that
we
should
forgive
those
who injured us. Alas! if
it were not for the reflection that I am not at
enmity
with any mortal breathing, how
should
I have hope
to obtain pardon of my Creator for the heinous
crime I have committed
whilst
in
pursuit
of my
