Hester
, and you know not
half the
anguish
of my
soul
.
My dear father,
said
she
, why will you give way
to unavailing
sorrow
? the kind Power who lent
him to you has but re-called his ownit is the lot
of mortalitythen, why my father, why will you
offend your Creator by repining at his divine will?
O,
Hester
, you do not know the dreadful
circumstances
of your brother's deathalas! my
child, he
rushed
unbidden into the prefence of his
Maker with multitudes of unrepented crimes upon
